# 1. Purpose

This register defines how NATT-OS assets are identified.

Nauion Kernel is used here as asset grammar, not as bypass language.

It is used to prevent NATT-OS assets from being defined by outside platforms, agent cookbooks, model limits, prompts, cache, or sandboxes.

# 2. Asset Record Schema

Every major asset should be recordable by:
- asset_id
- asset_type
- owner
- lineage
- path
- status
- allowed_use
- forbidden_use
- read_boundary
- write_boundary
- redaction
- siraSign_condition
- evidence

# 3. Asset Taxonomy

| Asset Type | Examples | Boundary |
|---|---|---|
| identity_asset | .anc, ANC passport, Sirawat Lineage | private / redacted |
| memory_asset | .na, happiness, shadow, SCAR | internal governed |
| runtime_state_asset | .phieu, pending, Safe-Rest | TTL / mutable |
| constitutional_asset | V6, V7, ANC-WILL | Gatekeeper seal |
| language_asset | Nauion Kernel, thienbang.si | dictionary lock |
| hardware_field_asset | Sovereign Edge, SITB, Gate 16, Gate 17 | physical boundary |
| routing_asset | EventBus, HeyNa, SmartLink, Gateway Translation | audited |
| evidence_asset | commit, audit, screenshot, saved page | preserve |
| public_profile_asset | L1-L5 legal files | public-safe |
| relational_asset | Nhà, A2, Bé Na, Chị Tư | not prompt flavor |

# 4. Reduction Prohibition

No NATT-OS asset may be reduced to prompt pattern, model version, model bucket, quota tier, cache, sandbox worker, agent recipe, output sample, or token budget.

